raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for the coordination and completion of projects. Oversees all aspects of projects. Sets deadlines, assigns responsibilities, and monitors and summarizes progress of project. Prepares reports for upper management regarding status of project. Familiar with a variety of the field’s concepts, practices, and procedures. Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Performs a wide variety of tasks. Leads and directs the work of others. A wide degree of creativity and latitude is expected.

raw_data.title: Field Technician I
raw_data.description: Perform non- routine and complex assignments under the general supervision of a project manager. May also assist in preparation of deliverables. Demonstrates familiarity with principles and precautions needed for the particular assignment. Can perform simple tasks under the supervision ofsenior personnel.

raw_data.title: Field Technician II
raw_data.description: Perform non- routine and complex assignments under the general supervision of a project manager. May also assist in preparation of deliverables. Demonstrates familiarity with principles and precautions needed for the particular assignment. Can perform more complex tasks with minimal supervision required.

raw_data.title: Field Technician III
raw_data.description: Perform non- routine and complex assignments. May also assist in preparation of deliverables. Demonstrates familiarity with principles and precautions needed for the particular assignment. Can perform all tasks with no supervision required. Shallsupervise junior personnel.

raw_data.title: Project Superintendent
raw_data.description: For assigned projects, completes project initiation documents which include detailed work scope, outline, budget, and schedule for completion. Fully competent engineer in all conventional aspects of subject matter or functional area of assignments. Plans and conducts work requiring judgment in independent evaluation, selection, and substantial adaptation or modification of standard techniques, procedures, and criteria. Manages project team to ensure that all work is completed as planned and scheduled. Responsible for Project Quality Control procedures and implementation.

raw_data.title: Project Coordinator
raw_data.description: Primarily provides support to the Project Superintendent in all facets of tracking, coordinating, and assisting in the completion of major programs and projects. Performs administrative tasks and completes administrative requirements.

raw_data.title: Senior Engineer
raw_data.description: Fully competent engineer in all conventional aspects of subject matter or functional area of assignments. Must be capable of performing and/or supervising all tasks and staff below this category. Establishes and controls project schedules and critical path for completion. Has full responsibility for interpreting, organizing, executing, and coordinating assignments. Plans and conducts work requiring judgment in independent evaluation, selection, and substantial adaptation or modification of standard techniques, procedures, and criteria. Devises new solutions to problems encountered. Independently performs most assignments with instruction only regarding general expected results. Provides technical guidance for unusual or complex problems and supervisory oversight and approval of proposed project plans, specifications and drawings. Can supervise engineers and technicians.

raw_data.title: Junior Engineer
raw_data.description: Establishes and controls project schedules and critical path for completion. Has full responsibility for interpreting, organizing, executing, and coordinating assignments. Plans and conducts work requiring judgment in independent evaluation, selection, and substantial adaptation or modification of standard techniques, procedures, and criteria. Devises new solutions to problems encountered. Independently performs most assignments with instruction only regarding general expected results. Provides technical guidance for unusual or complex problems and supervisory oversight and approval of proposed project plans, specifications and drawings.

raw_data.title: Engineer Technician
raw_data.description: Performs routine design and commissioning tasks for various projects. Supervisory function is essentially administrative. Typical duties and responsibilities include planning, organization, and facilitation of technicians and other non-engineering staff.

raw_data.title: Senior Consultant
raw_data.description: Professional providing general guidance and assistance to help customers achieve a specific solution pertaining to energy management. Demonstrates exceptional oral and written communication skills. Has exceptional technical ability and high level of expertise in energy related disciplines. Reviews all technical deliverables, trains and mentors the company’s technical staff. Supervises junior personnel.

raw_data.title: Mid Consultant
raw_data.description: Professional providing general guidance and assistance to help customers achieve a specific solution pertaining to energy management. Demonstrates exceptional oral and written communication skills. Has exceptional technical ability and high level of expertise in energy related disciplines. Reviews all technical deliverables, trains and mentors the company’s technical staff. Can supervise junior personnel.

raw_data.title: Junior Consultant
raw_data.description: Professional providing general guidance and assistance to help customers achieve a specific solution pertaining to energy management. Demonstrates exceptional oral and written communication skills. Has exceptional technical ability and high level of expertise in energy related disciplines. Reviews all technical deliverables, trains and mentors the company’s technical staff. Performs under general supervision.
